{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839885336,"sessionID":"ses_287b1fdb0ffeNCtszLkqEWTfOh","part":{"id":"prt_d784e35e3001BKbND49Hy3emGq","messageID":"msg_d784e2de7001dUq6quvSUjmlvE","sessionID":"ses_287b1fdb0ffeNCtszLkqEWTfOh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5697c4f6baa4401589aa77e1339a33f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: 定义 AgentRuntime 自定义资源定义（CRD），用于在 Kubernetes 中声明 agent 运行时实例的配置和状态。\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube 平台提供 AgentRuntime CRD 的 Go 类型定义，包括 API 组、版本、Schema 和 OpenAPI 验证规则。\n10: \n11: ## Module\n12: \n13: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n14: \n15: ## Language\n16: \n17: Go 1.24\n18: \n19: ## Size\n20: \n21: S\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: 1. **AgentRuntime CRD 类型定义**\n28:    - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API 组\n29:    - Namespaced 作用域\n30:    - Go 结构体定义（Spec 和 Status）\n31:    - OpenAPIV3Schema 验证规则\n32:    - 默认值设置\n33:    - 打印列（Age）\n34: \n35: 2. **Required Spec 字段**\n36:    - `maxSessionDuration` (string, 默认 \"8h\")\n37:    - `sessionTimeout` (string, 默认 \"15m\")\n38:    - `targetPort` (TargetPort 数组)\n39:    - `podTemplate` (PodTemplateSpec)\n40: \n41: 3. **Status 字段**\n42:    - Conditions 集合\n43:    - 其他状态信息\n44: \n45: ### Out of Scope\n46: \n47: - Controller 实现\n48: - Webhook 验证\n49: - CRD YAML 生成（由 controller-gen 处理）\n50: - CodeInterpreter CRD（AR-002）\n51: \n52: ## Impact Analysis\n53: \n54: ### Components Impacted\n55: \n56: 1. **Workload Manager**\n57:    - 需要读取 AgentRuntime 资源\n58:    - 基于 AgentRuntime spec 创建 agent-sandbox Sandbox\n59:    - 更新 AgentRuntime status\n60: \n61: 2. **Client-Go Library**\n62:    - 生成的 TypedClient 包含 AgentRuntimeInterface\n63:    - Informer factory 支持 AgentRuntime 监听\n64:    - Lister 提供 AgentRuntime 查询\n65: \n66: 3. **Helm Chart**\n67:    - CRD YAML 在 `manifests/charts/base/crds/` 下\n68:    - CRD 随 chart 生命周期安装\n69: \n70: 4. **RBAC**\n71:    - WorkloadManager ClusterRole 包含 `agentruntimes` 的读权限\n72:    - `agentruntimes/status` 的更新权限\n73: \n74: ### Dependencies\n75: \n76: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/apiserver/v1alpha1` (或类似的基础类型)\n77: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1`\n78: - `k8s.io/api/core/v1` (用于 PodSpec 引用)\n79: \n80: ## Design Decisions\n81: \n82: ### API Group and Version\n83: \n84: **选择**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n85: \n86: **理由**:\n87: - 遵循 Kubernetes API 组命名约定（域名反转）\n88: - `v1alpha1` 表示早期版本，允许未来变更\n89: - 与 CodeInterpreter CRD 共享 API 组\n90: \n91: ### Spec Fields 设计\n92: \n93: **maxSessionDuration**\n94: - 类型: `string`\n95: - 默认值: `\"8h\"`\n96: - 用途: 单个 agent 会话的最大持续时间\n97: \n98: **sessionTimeout**\n99: - 类型: `string`\n100: - 默认值: `\"15m\"`\n101: - 用途: 会话空闲超时时间\n102: \n103: **targetPort**\n104: - 类型: `[]TargetPort`\n105: - 必需字段: `port` (int32), `protocol` (enum: \"HTTP\"|\"HTTPS\")\n106: - 可选字段: `name` (string), `pathPrefix` (string)\n107: - 用途: 定义 agent 暴露的端口配置\n108: \n109: **podTemplate**\n110: - 类型: `PodTemplateSpec`\n111: - 必需字段: 是\n112: - 用途: 完整的 Pod spec 模板，用于创建 sandbox pod\n113: \n114: ### Status Fields 设计\n115: \n116: **conditions**\n117: - 类型: `[]Condition`\n118: - 用途: 记录资源状态转换和错误信息\n119: \n120: ### Validation Rules\n121: \n122: - 所有 required 字段通过 OpenAPIV3Schema enforce\n123: - 协议枚举通过 OpenAPI enum validation\n124: - 时长格式使用 Kubernetes Duration string\n125: \n126: ## Alternatives Considered\n127: \n128: ### Alternative 1: 使用独立的 API 组\n129: **描述**: AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter 使用不同的 API 组\n130: \n131: **优点**:\n132: - 完全隔离，独立演进\n133: \n134: **缺点**:\n135: - 增加复杂性\n136: - 违反单一职责原则（都是 runtime 资源）\n137: - RBAC 配置更复杂\n138: \n139: **选择**: 不采纳 - 使用共享 API 组更合理\n140: \n141: ### Alternative 2: 合并 Spec 字段\n142: **描述**: 将 maxSessionDuration 和 sessionTimeout 合并为一个配置对象\n143: \n144: **优点**:\n145: - 减少顶层字段数量\n146: \n147: **缺点**:\n148: - 增加嵌套层级\n149: - API 更复杂\n150: - 不符合 Kubernetes 简单优先原则\n151: \n152: **选择**: 不采纳 - 扁平化结构更清晰\n153: \n154: ### Alternative 3: 使用 v1 版本\n155: **描述**: 直接使用 v1 版本而非 v1alpha1\n156: \n157: **优点**:\n158: - 表示稳定性\n159: \n160: **缺点**:\n161: - 限制未来变更能力\n162: - v1alpha1 更适合早期阶段\n163: \n164: **选择**: 不采纳 - v1alpha1 更适合当前阶段\n165: \n166: ## Implementation Plan\n167: \n168: ### Phase 1: 类型定义 (Day 1)\n169: \n170: 1. 创建 `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` 目录结构\n171: 2. 定义 `AgentRuntimeSpec` 结构体\n172: 3. 定义 `AgentRuntimeStatus` 结构体\n173: 4. 定义 `AgentRuntime` 结构体（嵌入 metav1.TypeMeta 和 metav1.ObjectMeta）\n174: 5. 定义 `AgentRuntimeList` 结构体\n175: 6. 实现 `DeepCopy` 方法（通过 controller-gen 生成）\n176: \n177: ### Phase 2: OpenAPI 验证 (Day 2)\n178: \n179: 1. 添加 marker 注释\n180: 2. 定义 `// +kubebuilder:printcolumn` 用于 Age 列\n181: 3. 设置默认值\n182: 4. 配置 required 字段\n183: 5. 配置 enum 验证\n184: \n185: ### Phase 3: 注册和 Scheme (Day 2)\n186: \n187: 1. 创建 `register.go` 注册 API group\n188: 2. 创建 `groupversion_info.go` 定义 GroupVersion\n189: 3. 在 Scheme 中注册类型\n190: \n191: ### Phase 4: 代码生成 (Day 2)\n192: \n193: 1. 运行 `make gen-crd` 生成 CRD YAML\n194: 2. 运行 `make gen-client` 生成 client-go 代码\n195: 3. 验证生成的代码\n196: \n197: ## Testing Strategy\n198: \n199: ### Unit Tests\n200: \n201: 1. **类型验证测试**\n202:    - 验证 Spec 和 Status 结构体定义正确\n203:    - 测试默认值应用\n204: \n205: 2. **DeepCopy 测试**\n206:    - 验证 DeepCopy 方法正确复制所有字段\n207:    - 验证不会修改原对象\n208: \n209: 3. **JSON 序列化测试**\n210:    - 验证 JSON 序列化/反序列化正确\n211:    - 验证 omitempty 字段行为\n212: \n213: ### CRD 验证\n214: \n215: 1. **OpenAPI 验证**\n216:    - 使用 `kubectl apply --dry-run` 验证 CRD\n217:    - 测试 required 字段验证\n218:    - 测试 enum 验证\n219:    - 测试默认值应用\n220: \n221: 2. **创建测试**\n222:    - 创建有效的 AgentRuntime 资源\n223:    - 尝试创建无效资源（缺失 required 字段）\n224: \n225: ## Open Questions\n226: \n227: 1. **Q1**: Status 中是否需要更多状态字段？\n228:    - **当前**: 仅 conditions\n229:    - **讨论**: 可能需要 lastTransitionTime, observedGeneration 等\n230:    - **决策**: 初始使用标准 conditions，后续根据需求扩展\n231: \n232: 2. **Q2**: podTemplate 是否应该限制某些字段？\n233:    - **当前**: 完整的 PodTemplateSpec\n234:    - **讨论**: 某些字段可能不应该被用户修改\n235:    - **决策**: 初始允许完整 spec，通过 webhook 后置验证限制\n236: \n237: ## References\n238: \n239: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n240: - [Kubebuilder CRD Best Practices](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/generating-crd.html)\n241: - [AgentCube Design Document](../deployment/design.md)\n242: - [AgentCube Specification](../deployment/spec.md)\n\n(End of file - total 242 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Overview\n\n定义 AgentRuntime 自定义资源定义（CRD），用于在 Kubernetes 中声明 agent 运行时实例的配置和状态。\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube 平台提供 AgentRuntime CRD 的 Go 类型定义，包括 API 组、版本、Schema 和 OpenAPI 验证规则。\n\n## Module\n\n`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n## Language\n\nGo 1.24\n\n## Size\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839885314,"end":1775839885334}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839885352,"sessionID":"ses_287b1fdb0ffeNCtszLkqEWTfOh","part":{"id":"prt_d784e37e70018C6ECMAOIGgroB","messageID":"msg_d784e2de7001dUq6quvSUjmlvE","sessionID":"ses_287b1fdb0ffeNCtszLkqEWTfOh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0a9758c3cd2d495eaf30018ef4c865e8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package v1alpha1\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n5: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/intstr\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: // +genclient\n9: // +genclient:nonNamespaced\n10: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n11: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n12: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar;agentruntime\n13: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n14: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n15: \n16: // AgentRuntime defines a custom resource for managing agent runtime configurations.\n17: // It represents a sandbox orchestration runtime that manages the lifecycle of agent pods.\n18: type AgentRuntime struct {\n19: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n20: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n21: \n22: \tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n23: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n24: }\n25: \n26: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime.\n27: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n28: \t// PodTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n29: \t// +required\n30: \tPodTemplate *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\"`\n31: \n32: \t// SessionTimeout defines the timeout for idle sessions before cleanup.\n33: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n34: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n35: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n36: \t// +optional\n37: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n38: \n39: \t// MaxSessionDuration defines the maximum allowed duration for a session.\n40: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n41: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n42: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n43: \t// +optional\n44: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n45: }\n46: \n47: // SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n48: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n49: \t// Metadata defines labels and annotations for the pod.\n50: \t// +optional\n51: \tMetadata *SandboxMetadata `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n52: \n53: \t// Spec defines the pod specification.\n54: \tSpec SandboxPodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n55: }\n56: \n57: // SandboxMetadata defines metadata for sandbox pods.\n58: type SandboxMetadata struct {\n59: \t// Labels are key-value pairs attached to the pod.\n60: \t// +optional\n61: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n62: \n63: \t// Annotations are unstructured key-value pairs stored with the pod.\n64: \t// +optional\n65: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: // SandboxPodSpec defines the specification for sandbox pods.\n69: type SandboxPodSpec struct {\n70: \t// Containers represents the list of containers in the pod.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n72: \tContainers []SandboxContainer `json:\"containers\"`\n73: \n74: \t// NodeSelector specifies node selection constraints.\n75: \t// +optional\n76: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n77: \n78: \t// Affinity defines pod scheduling constraints.\n79: \t// +optional\n80: \tAffinity *SandboxAffinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n81: \n82: \t// Tolerations defines pod tolerations.\n83: \t// +optional\n84: \tTolerations []SandboxToleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n85: \n86: \t// ResourceRequirements defines resource requirements for the pod.\n87: \t// +optional\n88: \tResourceRequirements *SandboxResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n89: \n90: \t// Volumes defines pod volumes.\n91: \t// +optional\n92: \tVolumes []SandboxVolume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: // SandboxContainer defines a container in a sandbox pod.\n96: type SandboxContainer struct {\n97: \t// Name is the name of the container.\n98: \t// +required\n99: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n100: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n101: \n102: \t// Image is the container image.\n103: \t// +required\n104: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n105: \n106: \t// Command specifies the entrypoint array for the container.\n107: \t// +optional\n108: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n109: \n110: \t// Args specifies the arguments to the entrypoint.\n111: \t// +optional\n112: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n113: \n114: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory.\n115: \t// +optional\n116: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n117: \n118: \t// Ports represents the network ports exposed by the container.\n119: \t// +optional\n120: \tPorts []SandboxContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n121: \n122: \t// Env represents environment variables.\n123: \t// +optional\n124: \tEnv []SandboxEnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n125: \n126: \t// Resources defines compute resource requirements.\n127: \t// +optional\n128: \tResources *SandboxContainerResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// VolumeMounts specifies volume mounts.\n131: \t// +optional\n132: \tVolumeMounts []SandboxVolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n133: \n134: \t// LivenessProbe defines the liveness probe.\n135: \t// +optional\n136: \tLivenessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"livenessProbe,omitempty\"`\n137: \n138: \t// ReadinessProbe defines the readiness probe.\n139: \t// +optional\n140: \tReadinessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"readinessProbe,omitempty\"`\n141: \n142: \t// SecurityContext defines security settings.\n143: \t// +optional\n144: \tSecurityContext *SandboxSecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n145: }\n146: \n147: // SandboxContainerPort defines a network port in a container.\n148: type SandboxContainerPort struct {\n149: \t// Name is the name of the port.\n150: \t// +optional\n151: \tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n152: \n153: \t// ContainerPort is the port number on the container.\n154: \t// +required\n155: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n156: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n157: \tContainerPort int32 `json:\"containerPort\"`\n158: \n159: \t// Protocol is the protocol for the port.\n160: \t// +optional\n161: \t// +kubebuilder:default=TCP\n162: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n163: \n164: \t// HostPort is the port number on the host.\n165: \t// +optional\n166: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n167: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n168: \tHostPort int32 `json:\"hostPort,omitempty\"`\n169: }\n170: \n171: // SandboxEnvVar defines an environment variable.\n172: type SandboxEnvVar struct {\n173: \t// Name is the name of the environment variable.\n174: \t// +required\n175: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n176: \n177: \t// Value is the literal value of the environment variable.\n178: \t// +optional\n179: \tValue string `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n180: \n181: \t// ValueFrom specifies a source for the value.\n182: \t// +optional\n183: \tValueFrom *SandboxEnvVarSource `json:\"valueFrom,omitempty\"`\n184: }\n185: \n186: // SandboxEnvVarSource defines a source for environment variable values.\n187: type SandboxEnvVarSource struct {\n188: \t// FieldRef selects a field from the pod.\n189: \t// +optional\n190: \tFieldRef *SandboxFieldRef `json:\"fieldRef,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// ConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n193: \t// +optional\n194: \tConfigMapKeyRef *SandboxConfigMapKeyRef `json:\"configMapKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// SecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n197: \t// +optional\n198: \tSecretKeyRef *SandboxSecretKeyRef `json:\"secretKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n199: }\n200: \n201: // SandboxFieldRef selects a field from a pod.\n202: type SandboxFieldRef struct {\n203: \t// FieldPath is the path of the field.\n204: \t// +required\n205: \tFieldPath string `json:\"fieldPath\"`\n206: }\n207: \n208: // SandboxConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n209: type SandboxConfigMapKeyRef struct {\n210: \t// Name is the name of the ConfigMap.\n211: \t// +required\n212: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n213: \n214: \t// Key is the key to select.\n215: \t// +required\n216: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n217: \n218: \t// Optional specifies whether the ConfigMap must exist.\n219: \t// +optional\n220: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n221: }\n222: \n223: // SandboxSecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n224: type SandboxSecretKeyRef struct {\n225: \t// Name is the name of the Secret.\n226: \t// +required\n227: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n228: \n229: \t// Key is the key to select.\n230: \t// +required\n231: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n232: \n233: \t// Optional specifies whether the Secret must exist.\n234: \t// +optional\n235: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n236: }\n237: \n238: // SandboxContainerResources defines resource requirements for a container.\n239: type SandboxContainerResources struct {\n240: \t// Limits defines the resource limits.\n241: \t// +optional\n242: \tLimits SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n243: \n244: \t// Requests defines the resource requests.\n245: \t// +optional\n246: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n247: }\n248: \n249: // SandboxResourceList defines a list of resources.\n250: type SandboxResourceList struct {\n251: \t// CPU defines CPU resources.\n252: \t// +optional\n253: \tCPU string `json:\"cpu,omitempty\"`\n254: \n255: \t// Me